Key Match Events: Giddey put the game to bed with two clutch free throws with 14 seconds remaining
Post-Match Reflections: The Bulls ended the year on a two-game winning streak, improving to 15-18 for the season. They currently sit ninth in the Eastern Conference standings and are primed to finish in the Play-In Tournament spots.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bulls were much better in the second quarter, finally making shots and even getting the lead at the 5:08 mark.
Giddey added seven points to his tally, including two late free throws toward the end of the half to give Chicago a 52-46 advantage.
